additional_info:
Or use this in file <a href="http://kb.mozillazine.org/UserContent.css" title="http://kb.mozillazine.org/UserContent.css"><b>userContent.css</b></a>:
<ul><li> ⬤ Firefox 67 - 87:
<code><pre>:-moz-autofill, :autofill, :-moz-autofill-preview {
  filter: unset
}</pre></code><li> ⬤ Firefox 88/89 (and maybe 90-93 with 91 ESR) need use remove CSS filters from all inputs:

<code><pre>:root input {
    filter: unset
}</pre></code> <li> ⬤ Firefox 94+ started use css background (and maybe have plans use "shadow efects"):

<code><pre>:root input:autofill {
	border: 1px solid grey;
	border-radius: 3px;
	padding: 2px;
	background-image: unset
}
</pre></code></ul>

(I don't know how support :autofill pseudoclass start works in addon)

css:
/* i really want this to be global */
/* css for Stylus / xStyle / rather Stylish */

@-moz-document url-prefix("http") {
:root input:autofill {
    border: 1px solid grey;
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 2px;
    background-image: unset
}


@supports (filter: revert) {
:root input {
    filter: none
}

}

/* works only from userContent.css file (FX 67 - 87) - latter may support use pseudoclasses:
:-moz-autofill, :autofill, :-moz-autofill-preview {
    filter: unset
}
*/
}

